[2] Viet Nam (national)
Date: Wed 26 Nov 2008
Source: VietNamNet Bridge, Tien Phong Online report [edited]
<http://english.vietnamnet.vn/social/2008/11/815476/>


The Health Ministry said on Monday [24 Nov 2008] that more than 78
500 dengue fever cases were recorded so far this year [2008], with 79
people who died.

The number of dengue fever patients in October [2008] grew by over 20
percent while the number of deaths was reduced by 7 year on year.

In November [2008], the disease spread widely in many provinces and
cities, totaling 15 000 new cases, 15 deaths.

The Hanoi Department of Health said Hanoi had nearly 1700 patients in
November [2008] with no deaths.

Dengue fever patients in the capital city [Hanoi] live in 170
communes and wards of 21 districts. Around 81 percent of them are in
the inner city and 89 percent are adults.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur A-Lan Banks

[ProMED-MBDS cites a report from the Xinhua News Agency dated 25 Nov 2008
(<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-11/25/content_10409901.htm>)
that the recent floods in northern provinces and the ongoing floods
in central and southern provinces of Viet Nam have created stagnant
bodies of water and perfect breeding grounds for the mosquitoes,
causing the spread of the disease [virus].

Maps of Viet Nam with provinces can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_admin01.jpg>
and <http://www.angelfire.com/co/hongnam/vnmap.html>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Viet Nam can be accessed
at <http://healthmap.org/promed?v=14.9,108.5,5>. This map shows other
outbreaks in Viet Nam and surrounding countries that have been
reported by ProMED-mail and PRO/MBDS. The postings can be directly
accessed through this map. - Mod.TY]

